Getting started with the SFTP driver
====================================

You can use a password or your private key to setup your SFTP Driver.

If you set a password in the setup.json file, the private_key_path and private_key_passphrase will be ignored.

All the defaults variables are optional:

password: ""
private_key_path: ~/.ssh/id_rsa
private_key_passphrase: ""
port: 22

An example of setup.json which use a private key (uses the default value) with an empty password (default value), a default port.

{
  "name": "example",

  "entries": {
    "LOC": {
      "driver": "local_storage",
      "options": {
        "root": "example/loc"
      }
    },
    "FTP": {
      "driver": "sftp",
      "options": {
        "root": "/home/myname/sftp/",
        "hostname": "localhost",
        "username": "myname",
        "changes_timer": 10
      }
    }
  },

  "rules": [
    {
      "match": {"path": "/"},
      "sync": ["LOC", "FTP"]
    }
  ]

}
